er that includes `Annotation`, `Distance to TSS` (renamed\n`Distance.to.TSS` by R) and `Nearest PromoterID`.\n\nProduce:\n  - `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv`: a wide table (one row per sample) with the\n    count of peaks per first-token feature (exon, Intergenic, intron, promoter-TSS,\n    TTS, ...).\n  - `output/homer_annot.pdf`: a multi-page PDF containing (1) a stacked feature-\n    proportion barplot, (2) a stacked distance-bin barplot (<2kb/<5kb/<10kb/>10kb\n    based on each unique gene's closest peak) and (3) a log10 violin plot of the\n    `Distance.to.TSS` distribution per sample.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/homer_annot.pdf` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: homer_annot.pdf, homer_annot_summary.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_anno.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_anno.txt\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_anno.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_anno.txt\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_anno.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_anno.txt\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/homer_annot.pdf` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_qX8NveqnwzknfLDEmIqTn2Bt", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the input files `sampleA_anno.txt`, `sampleB_anno.txt`, and `sampleC_anno.txt` to understand their structure and contents.\\n2. Process each file to extract the necessary information for the summary table and plots:\\n   - Count the number of peaks per feature (first-token of `Annotation`).\\n   - Determine the distance to TSS for each peak and categorize them into bins (<2kb, <5kb, <10kb, >10kb).\\n3. Create a summary table `homer_annot_summary.tsv` with the count of peaks per feature for each sample.\\n4. Generate a multi-page PDF `homer_annot.pdf` with the following plots:\\n   - A stacked feature-proportion barplot for each sample.\\n   - A stacked distance-bin barplot for each sample.\\n   - A log10 violin plot of the `Distance.to.TSS` distribution per sample.\\n5. Save the outputs in the `output/` directory.\\n6. Verify the existence of `homer_annot.pdf` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (911 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_qX8NveqnwzknfLDEmIqTn2Bt"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_3LYRCqy3fTnx9boj5J5dhlbN", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/sampleA_anno.txt\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_0iItXDa0cishkoSp4WyOvmOC", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/sampleB_anno.txt\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_lBmShPmWvuZRNbdNDqsswClW", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/sampleC_anno.txt\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "next_agent_state": {"tools": [{"type": "function", "info": {"name": "run_shell", "description": "Run a shell command in the task work_dir (bash -lc).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"command": {"description": "Shell command string passed to `bash -lc`.", "title": "Command", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["command"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "read_text_file", "description": "Read a UTF-8 text file relative to work_dir.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"relative_path": {"description": "Path under the workspace (not absolute).", "title": "Relative Path", "type": "string"}